name: GobletoftheSojourner
desc: A plain porcelain goblet that was once brimming with joyous brews.

name: FeatherofHomecoming
desc: A blue arrow fletching imbued with the sentiment of travelers that had once faded into the horizon.

name: CrownofParting
desc: A reed coronet that emanates the spring breeze.

name: HeartofComradeship
desc: A small cerulean flower with somebody's ribbon pinned to the stem.

name: SundialoftheSojourner
desc: A sundial that has survived the ages, always silently recording the cycles of the sun and moon as they pass through the sky.

name: MedaloftheBrave
desc: A simple flower brooch that is a keepsake from someone's first adventure.

desc: A feather-shaped brooch that symbolizes someone’s yearning to defend others like a shield.

name: GuardiansBand
desc: A fabric band dyed indigo by the darkness of night. Can also double as a bandage in the event of an emergency.

name: GuardiansFlower
desc: An iris that was cherished by the guardian. Unfortunately, the chance never came for it to be given to whom the guardian loved.

name: GuardiansClock
desc: A small timekeeping gadget. On moonless nights, it was the only way its former owner could know the time.

name: TinyMiraclesFeather
desc: A feather from a bird of prey that flies almost too fast for the human eye to detect.

name: TinyMiraclesEarrings
desc: A cheap accessory that is actually made from ancient meteoric ore.

name: TinyMiraclesFlower
desc: A flower that grew from a rock, breaking through the stone as it strove to reach the light.

name: TinyMiraclesHourglass
desc: Just an ordinary, everyday hourglass. Turn it upside down and sure enough, the dry sand starts trickling down like water.

name: BerserkersBattleMask
desc: A hideous iron mask that has been left half-shattered from vicious battles.

name: BerserkersRose
desc: An exquisite flower that has been dyed red. It represents the qualities of the Berserker.

name: BerserkersTimepiece
desc: An instrument with an eternal flow that continues mercilessly within, reminding the Berserker of the limited time he has left — both on the battlefield as well as in the world.

name: MartialArtistsFeatherAccessory
desc: A common bird feather. Experts use it to practice strength control, while rookies use it to make fans.

name: MartialArtistsBandana
desc: The first lesson as an apprentice: Vigor, Strength, Will. These words are written on the bandana so you'll never forget them.

name: MartialArtistsRedFlower
desc: This particular kind of red flower was the only thing that could alleviate the Martial Artist's pain.

name: MartialArtistsWaterHourglass

desc: It may seem like an ordinary tea cup to most. But to students, it is the symbol of the instructor's authority.

name: InstructorsFeatherAccessory
desc: Any instructor who has mastered the art of de-escalation knows to keep this accessory firmly in their grasp at all times.

name: InstructorsCap
desc: A standard-issue honorary instructor's cap, only granted to those who turn down a promotion.

name: InstructorsBrooch
desc: Whenever the instructor wore this brooch, it meant there would be no training sessions that day.

name: InstructorsPocketWatch
desc: A stopwatch used not for general timekeeping but to measure the duration of a training session.

name: GamblersEarrings
desc: A pair of blue earrings that, when worn, calm the mind and encourage a rational assessment of risks.

name: GamblersBrooch
desc: A big, luxurious flower that can hide a loaded dice.

name: ExilesFeather
desc: Not an actual accessory per se. Just a random bird feather that was found somewhere in the wilderness by the exile.

name: ExilesCirclet
desc: A prestigious circlet. However, the royal insignia has been scratched out, and it is no longer the symbol of distinguished status that it once was.

name: ExilesFlower
desc: A withered flower worn on the shirt. Its former owner insisted on wearing it even in exile, so it must mean something.

name: ExilesPocketWatch
desc: Even after the crystal watch face was shattered and the hands lost, its former owner kept it until the end.

desc: The spoils of one of an adventurer's many expeditions. Though a little damaged, it is still an excellent find.

name: AdventurersTailFeather
desc: The feather of an exotic bird rarely seen on this continent.

name: AdventurersBandana
desc: A cloth garment worn at the forehead. Though soaked in sweat and covered in dust, it still beams with an adventurer's pride.

name: AdventurersFlower
desc: A resilient flower that survived the harsh environment of an ancient city. It is now proudly worn like a medal.

name: AdventurersPocketWatch
desc: It's easy to lose track of time when you're adventuring where the sun doesn't shine, whether that's the depths of the abyss or the ruins of a lost city.

desc: An exquisite metallic vessel that was once used to knock out a thief.

name: LuckyDogsEagleFeather
desc: A monster once cornered an adventurer, but was then picked off by a hunting eagle... That eagle dropped this feather, which now carries some of the adventurer's good luck.

name: LuckyDogsSilverCirclet
desc: Its former owner once fell into a cave and found the treasure trove of an exiled royal. This is a souvenir from that incident.

name: LuckyDogsClover
desc: A four-leaf clover that grows in the wild. It was picked because it is said to bring good luck.

name: LuckyDogsHourglass
desc: A broken hourglass from which all the sand has escaped. But it's fine, because the passage of time means nothing to someone without a single worry in the whole world.

desc: Originally designed to hold drinking water, this cup was stained black after a scholar used it to wash their paint brushes.

name: ScholarsQuillPen
desc: A bird's feather that serves as a quill pen. The tip has long been stained black.

name: ScholarsLens
desc: This corrective lens helped restore the vision of one whose eyes were damaged from intensive studying.

name: ScholarsBookmark
desc: A dried flower used as a bookmark. It has absorbed the scent from the pages.

name: ScholarsClock
desc: A small desktop clock, whose former owner was a scholar sat in a windowless room buried in books. This was probably the only reference they had to the time of day.

desc: This pot used to carry concentrated and extremely potent concoctions. It is now empty, but still gives off a strong smell of medicine.

name: TravelingDoctorsOwlFeather
desc: The durable feather of an owl. Emblematic of nocturnal supremacy, it gave some encouragement to the Traveling Doctor when venturing out to visit patients late at night.

name: TravelingDoctorsHandkerchief
desc: Used to tie back the doctor's hair when treating patients. Can also be used as a sling for sprains and broken arms in emergencies.

name: TravelingDoctorsSilverLotus
desc: A precious medicinal ingredient that has lost all medicinal value after years in storage.

name: TravelingDoctorsPocketWatch
desc: A precise instrument used for keeping time. For a doctor, every second counts.

name: FrostWeavedDignity
desc: A cup carved out of ice that is as chilly and biting as winter. Its former master would drink an unfreezable liquor from it.

name: IcebreakersResolve
desc: A feather that exudes a chilly aura. One can almost feel the turbulent winds that brought it here, wailing over snow-covered plains and between frosty peaks.

name: BrokenRimesEcho
desc: The crown of an ancient hero who dreamt of conquering the cold. It is proof of its former master's bravery in facing the bone-chilling cold of winter.

name: SnowsweptMemory
desc: A long-extinct flower, covered in beads of frost, that once grew on the glaciers. There was a time when even the proudest and most arrogant warriors bowed before it.

name: FrozenHomelandsDemise
desc: A timepiece from a nation of old that waited for their warriors' return. What flows inside is not sand, but bits of ice that never melt.

desc: The wine goblet from which the Thundersoother, who defeated the Beast of Thunder, once drank violet lightning.

name: ThundersoothersPlume
desc: The feather of a predatory bird that soars through lightning storms. It was said to have been adopted as an insignia by the legendary hero who pacified thunder and lightning.

name: ThundersoothersDiadem
desc: The crown given to the Thundersoother for defeating the Beast of Thunder that had been wreaking havoc upon the land.

name: ThundersoothersHeart
desc: A flower that blooms even amidst ferocious thunder and lightning. To this day, it still grants courage to travelers in thunderstorms.

name: HourofSoothingThunder
desc: A timepiece kept by the hero who conquered thunder and lightning. The tiny shards of Electro crystal within flow back and forth with the passing of time.

desc: A legendary goblet that can withstand extremely high temperatures. It still retains a degree of warmth even though it is now empty.

name: LavawalkersSalvation
desc: The feather of a proud phoenix. You can almost hear the sound of its wings flapping in the scorching flames.

name: LavawalkersWisdom
desc: The circlet of a sage who traversed a sea of fire. It once shone brightly from their ancient silhouette as they stood strong amidst the flames.

name: LavawalkersResolution
desc: A flower that blooms amidst burning flames. It is said that long ago, a sage once wore it as he walked into a sea of fire.

name: LavawalkersTorment
desc: Burning sand flows within this hourglass. Despite the intense heat, the sand leave no mark upon the vessel that houses it.

desc: A vessel made with sweet black tea in mind rather than bitter liquor.

name: MaidensHeartstrickenInfatuation
desc: A feathered accessory that carries the longing for a certain someone, like a migratory bird on the wind.

name: MaidensFadingBeauty
desc: A meticulously well-maintained woman's hat that keeps wrinkles safely out of sight.

name: MaidensDistantLove
desc: A fragrant flower that will bloom for all eternity and never wither.

name: MaidensPassingYouth
desc: The hands of time will never come to an end, but the same cannot not be said for those cherished years of the young maiden's life when she was doted upon.

desc: The golden cup a champion gladiator drank from in ancient times. It brimmed with his glory for years until the fateful day of his fall.

name: GladiatorsDestiny
desc: A feather of dreams that soars free like an eagle. At the end of the gladiator's legendary life, this parting gift was left upon his chest by a bird that knew true freedom.

name: GladiatorsTriumphus
desc: The helmet of a legendary gladiator from ancient times, who would proudly stretch out his bloodied arms to welcome the thunderous applause of his audience.

name: GladiatorsNostalgia
desc: No-one knows why the legendary gladiator wore this flower on his chest. It was the brutal warrior's only weakness.

name: GladiatorsLonging
desc: A timepiece that recorded the gladiator's days in the bloodstained Colosseum. To him, it counted down the days on his long road to freedom.

name: TroupesDawnlight
desc: A small flower-shaped insignia. If you listen carefully, you can almost hear a flute playing and voices singing.

name: ConcertsFinalHour
desc: An hourglass used to keep time during a band performance. It once made a crisp sound, but their performance has since ended.

name: OmenofThunderstorm
desc: A ceremonial cup that holds the blood of the innocent. It is brimming with the thundering fury of the prayers that echo within.

name: SurvivorofCatastrophe
desc: A lightning-charged feather that still flickers with the wrath of the Thunderbird's cruel retribution.

name: ThunderSummonersCrown
desc: A crown once worn by an ancient shaman who worshiped the Thunderbird. The capricious beast remained unmoved by the shaman's devotion.

name: ThunderbirdsMercy
desc: A lightning-infused flower, somehow spared the fate of being trodden underfoot or reduced to ash by the furious purple fire, making it the sole survivor on the day of disaster.

name: HourglassofThunder
desc: The hourglass used to foretell the coming of the Thunderbird by the tribe that worshiped it. It has fallen into eternal silence now that the tribe is no more.

name: WitchsHeartFlames
desc: A flame-spitting urn left behind by the Crimson Witch of Flames, who once dreamt of burning away all the demons in the world. The fire in the urn burns eternally, as did its former master.

name: WitchsEverBurningPlume
desc: A bird feather touched by the witch who once dreamt of burning away all the demons in the world. Its eternal flame burns hot.

name: WitchsScorchingHat
desc: A hat once worn by the witch who dreamt of burning away all of the demons in the world. The large brim blocked her sight.

name: WitchsFlowerofBlaze
desc: A flower touched by the witch who once dreamt of burning away all the demons in the world. The anonymous flames affectionately caress the hands of those who touch it.

name: WitchsEndTime
desc: A timepiece worn by the witch who dreamt of burning away all the demons in the world. The years the witch dedicated to the flames flow within.

name: RoyalSilverUrn
desc: An ornamental urn that once belonged to the old aristocrats of Mondstadt. Mournful winds seem to echo within its empty interior.

name: RoyalPlume
desc: A feathered hat accessory worn by the old aristocrats of Mondstadt on hunts. It still stands proudly as if no time has passed.

name: RoyalMasque
desc: A masquerade mask worn by the old aristocrats of Mondstadt. Its hollow eyes are fixated on the golden days of the past.

name: RoyalFlora
desc: A satin flower with a glossy finish, fit for an elegant gathering. It still looks as distinguished as it did on the day it was cast aside.

name: RoyalPocketWatch
desc: A pocket watch that once belonged to the old aristocrats of Mondstadt. Passed down from generation to generation, it has witnessed many years of history.

name: BloodstainedChevaliersGoblet
desc: The dark metallic vessel owned by the Bloodstained Knight. Its exterior has been stained as black as the night by smoke and coagulated blood.

name: BloodstainedBlackPlume
desc: A raven feather pinned to a knight's cape. Countless bloodstains have dyed it pitch black.

name: BloodstainedIronMask
desc: The iron mask the knight used to conceal their identity. Many have speculated about the face behind the mask.

name: BloodstainedFlowerofIron
desc: A dried flower stained black with blood and now as hard as steel. Probably some sort of a memento for its former master.

name: BloodstainedFinalHour
desc: A timepiece once used by a knight. The liquid inside has dried up, rendering it useless.

name: TiaraofFlame
desc: A tiara worn by those tasked with offering sacrifices in ancient times. After being subjected to the dancing sacrificial flames year in and year out, it possesses remarkable resistance.

name: TiaraofTorrents
desc: A tiara worn by those tasked with offering sacrifices in ancient times. Because it was submerged in water year in and year out, it possesses remarkable resistance.

name: TiaraofTorrents
desc: A tiara worn by those tasked with offering sacrifices in ancient times. Because it was submerged in water year in and year out, it possesses remarkable resistance.

name: TiaraofThunder
desc: A tiara worn by those tasked with offering sacrifices in ancient times. Because it harkened to the call of thunder year in and year out, it possesses remarkable resistance.

desc: A tiara worn by those tasked with offering sacrifices in ancient times. Because it harkened to the call of thunder year in and year out, it possesses remarkable resistance.

name: TiaraofFrost
desc: A tiara worn by those tasked with offering sacrifices in ancient times. Because it once weathered years of the icy cold, it possesses remarkable resistance.

name: GobletofChiseledCrag
desc: A resplendent yet dignified wine goblet, once filled to the brim in an era long gone.

name: FeatherofJaggedPeaks
desc: A hard feather from a large seacliff hawk. The basalt tip of the feather sometimes glistens with a cool dew.

name: MaskofSolitudeBasalt
desc: A solemn mask exquisitely carved from basalt. Its hollow eyes stare ahead expressionless and cold.

name: FlowerofCrevicedCliff
desc: A flower born of the minerals and rocks of cliffside cracks. The way its petals blow in the wind makes it seem alive.

name: SundialofEnduringJade
desc: A sundial carved from a single, large piece of jade. Its lined with a pattern that silently records the passage of time.

name: SummerNightsWaterballoon
desc: Water balloons can be seen everywhere during the summer festival, but none are as finely-wrought as this one.

name: SummerNightsFinale
desc: A well-crafted wooden dart. It will only stop once it has reached its destination.

name: SummerNightsMask
desc: A popular mask cast in the image of a deity, as described in the legends.

name: SummerNightsBloom
desc: A man-made flower in eternal bloom. Who knows if there truly is life in there?

name: SummerNightsMoment
desc: A pocketwatch that has stopped at a certain point in time.

name: GobletofThunderingDeep
desc: A faded wine cup that was unintentionally dredged up from the sea. Its dull exterior tells of the days it has spent beneath the waves.

name: GustofNostalgia
desc: A feather carried over by whimpering sea winds and crimson waves. The passage of time has changed its shape and color.

name: WineStainedTricorne
desc: An ancient, wine-stained sea hat that still reeks of alcohol even now.

name: GildedCorsage
desc: A mantle brooch that has lost its luster. The gold plating that once adorned it was ground away by the wind and the waves long ago.

name: CopperCompass
desc: An ancient bronze compass. Its needle points towards some ever-distant shore, to a non-existent harbor.
